3. Which information we may collect on our Users?
We may collect two types of data and information from our Users:
a. Non-personal Information.
The first type is non-identifiable and anonymous information. Non-personal information, which is being gathered, consists of technical information and behavioral information that does not pertain to a specific individual (“
Non-Personal Information
”).
Like most online services, when you access and use the Site and/or App we passively collect certain Non-Personal Information from your devices (depending on whether you access our Site or App), including: (i) technical information such as the type and version of your device and its operating system, the type of browser, screen resolution, device browser and keyboard language, Wi-Fi connectivity and the type and name of your device and/or browser, etc.; and (ii) behavioral information which may include the User’s click-stream on the Site or App, the activities of the User on the App and/or Site and additional information of a similar nature (collectively, “
Technical and Behavioral Information
”). We may use third-party service providers to obtain detailed analytics on the device and the User's behavior on the Site and/or App. Please note that we or our third-party service providers will collect such Technical and Behavioral Information by using certain tracking technologies, such as cookies, as further detailed below.
b. Personal Information.
The second type of information is individually identifiable information (“
Personal Information
”).
This information may identify an individual or may be of a private and/or sensitive nature.
Personal Information which is provided voluntarily:
Communications:
Personal Information is collected from the details that Users may provide as part of any communications with Boards, by any means, including by e-mail, telephone, social media or otherwise. Such Personal Information may include your name and contact details and any other information which you may voluntarily provide to us.
Mailing list:
You may voluntarily provide us with your contact details in order to subscribe to our newsletter and to receive commercial materials from Boards and our partners. You can unsubscribe from our mailing list by using the instruction included in the communications sent to you, or by contacting us directly using the contact information provided in the "Contact Us" section of this Privacy Policy.
Registration to the App:
Personal Information is collected from the details the Users provide in the registration form available on the App (which enables the Users to open an Account), which includes, inter alia, name (including username), email and profile photo. Additional information may be requested in the future.
Important note:
Users’ names and nicknames may be made publicly available via the App, including to other Users. Please act with caution when selecting your nickname.
User Content:
Personal Information includes any data and/or content, including User Generated Content (as defined in our TOU), that you may upload or generate through use of the App, including without limitation boards created via the App, comments, information derived from your interactions with other Users, etc.
Please note:
if the Personal Information you provide to us includes information about others, you are fully and solely responsible for providing all necessary information notices to affected data subjects and obtaining any required consents under applicable privacy laws from data subjects for the use, processing, sub-processing and storing of their information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
Forms and Store:
The App allows registered Users to create Forms, and Users may disseminate links to such Forms to third parties (such as potential customers) via the App or otherwise. Information uploaded by Users of the Form to the Forms may include Personal Information, such as contact information and information relating to the purchase of products via the Form.
Please note that Board operates such Forms on behalf of the applicable User (i.e., the User who generated the Form), and all information uploaded to the Form will be made accessible to the such User and may be processed by such User at its sole discretion and in accordance with such User’s independent privacy policy. Board is not responsible for Users' independent processing of Personal Information collected via the Forms, or otherwise. Board disclaims all representations and warranties with respect to the independent processing of Personal Information by such Users and shall not be liable for any damage that you, or any third party, may incur as a result of Users' independent processing of Personal Information.
Important note: providing Personal Information via Forms is made at your discretion and at your sole risk – please exercise caution, as is generally expected when providing personal details online.
Depending on the nature of the Form, we may also process certain Personal Information collected via the Form for the purposes of providing our Services to the User. For example, if the Form is used by the User to operate an online store, all information collected via the Form will be made available to the applicable User. Additionally, we may use the information to collect payment on behalf of the User, as further detailed below in this Privacy Policy.
Payments:
for payment for our Services, or otherwise clearing payments via Forms, you will have the option to use certain Online Payment Processors which will require you to fill out a billing form wherein you will be required to provide to such Online Payment Processors certain Personal Information (such as, a credit card number and other related billing information). We will not store such information on our servers. We only keep token information such Online Payment Processors provide us with (and where applicable, the last four digits of your credit card number), and such information is strictly secured.
Application to the Boards Advisor Program:
When you submit an application to participate in the Boards Advisor Program (as further detailed in the TOU) you may be required to provide certain personal information, such as your country of residence, what you do for living, which languages you speak, your relevant skills and preferences, links to your profiles on social networks platforms, etc. Please note that participants in the Boards Advisor Program may be required to provide their photos and other personal data, as further detailed in the Program T&C.
Personal Information is collected also via technology
:
IP/MAC Address:
Users of the App and Site may automatically provide their IP address (or Mac Address, as applicable) and/or advertiser identifier (when available on a device) mainly for enhancing the User’s experience and for geo-location and security purposes, as well as for targeted advertising purposes.
Geolocation data:
while using the Site and/or the App we will access, collect, process, monitor and/or remotely store “geolocation data”, including through the collection of IP addresses and other similar information to determine your location for analytics and security purposes, as well as for targeted advertising purposes.
Technical and Behavioral Information:
to the extent that the Technical and Behavioral Information detailed above under Section 3.(a) will be linked to or associated with a specific individual, then such information will be considered as Personal Information.
Identifiers:
we process certain online identifiers, such as Internet Protocol (IP) address, your Unique Device Identifier (UDID), or another unique identifiers, for geo-location, targeted advertising and security purposes. In addition, when using the Site and/or the App, our authorized third-party service providers may collect your advertising identifiers, as further detailed below.
Please note that we use third-party tracking services and usage logs, to track and analyze data from Users of the Site and/or the App for purposes of security and fraud prevention. We may also use cookies to gather information regarding your use of the Site and/or the App and the information for which you searched and accessed.
Important Note:
We may cross-reference Personal Information with other Personal Information we have about you and any Non-personal Information connected or linked to or associated with any Personal Information shall be deemed as Personal Information as long as such connection, linkage or association exists. For avoidance of doubt, any Non-Personal Information connected or linked to any Personal Information shall be deemed as Personal Information, as long as such connection or linkage exists.
We do not collect any Personal Information from you or related to you without your approval, which is obtained, inter alia, through your active acceptance of the TOU and the Privacy Policy.
4. How Do We Collect Information on Our Users?
There are a few main methods we use:
a. We collect information through your entry, connection, installation, access and/or use of the App and entry, access and/or use of the Site.
In other words, when you are using the Services, we are aware of it and may gather, collect and store the information relating to such usage.
b. We collect information which you provide us voluntarily.
For example, we collect Personal Information when you register and open an Account.
Information collected from other Users and our business partners.
Users may upload to the App Personal Information relating to other Users and third parties. For example, if they wish to send links to their Forms to third parties, they may provide us with such third parties' email addresses. Upon accessing the Form, such third parties' use of the Form will become subject to this Privacy Policy. Furthermore, Users may be invited to use the App by our business partners. To facilitate this, our business partners may share with us certain information related to such Users (e.g., to assist in their onboarding to the App and associating their Account on the App with our applicable business partner's account).
We may gather, collect and store such information either independently or through the help of our authorized third-party service providers, as detailed below.
5. What are the Purposes of the Collection of Information?
a. Non-personal Information is collected in order to
:
Use it for statistical, analytical and research purposes and for customization, developing and improvement of the Site and/or App and/or Services.
Enhance the User's experience while using the Site and/or App and/or Services.
Keep the Site and/or the App safe and secured and for prevention of fraud.
b. Personal Information is collected and processed for the following purposes:
Personal Information collected via the Site, via technology, Users' App account information (including information collected when registering to the App), Technical and Behavioral Information (to the extent that it constitutes Personal Information), and Personal Information included in communications with Board are used for:
Operation of the App and Site and provision of the Services;
Transactional communications;
Personalization of business offerings;
Identifying Users and allowing access to the App;
Securing the App and Site and your account on the App, and prevention of fraud and crime (including phone validation);
Collection of subscription fees, where applicable;
Providing analytics to our business partners and other Users whose accounts on the App have been integrated with your account;
Allowing Users to participate in the Board Advisor Program, including examining applications submitted for the Board Advisor Program and considering the suitability of applicants to such program;
Providing Users with updates about the Company's developments, new offerings, and news regarding the Company, the App and the Services;
Sending push notifications to the User's device after the User has agreed to accept push notifications from Board. Users can deactivate push notifications by changing their settings within our Services;
Contacting Users for the purpose of providing them with the Site's or App's technical assistance and support;
Conducting internal operations, including troubleshooting, data analysis, testing, research, and statistical purposes, in order to improve our Site, App and Services. Please note that in general we analyze aggregate data for such purposes, rather than specific user data; however, we may need to analyze a specific case to address a specific problem;
Determining general geolocation information (i.e., country) from which the User's computer or device is connected to the Internet in order for us to know the general location of our App's Users as well as to safeguard our App;
Advertising and marketing (including sending newsletters and conducting targeted advertising and cross-platform advertising, subject to your consent where required by law);
Protecting the Company's rights and defense against legal claims;
Maintaining data processing records; and
Complying with legal requirements.
Any Personal Information uploaded to the App and/or Forms, or otherwise collected via the Forms:
Providing the
App and Services to Users (including providing the Services to visitors of the Forms, who are not registered Users of the App);
Hosting and operating the Forms on behalf of Users;
Providing analytics to our business partners and other Users whose accounts on the App have been integrated with your account;
Conducting internal operations such as troubleshooting, data analysis, testing, research, and statistical purposes to improve the Company's App, including by anonymizing the relevant data;
Complying with legal requirements;
Maintaining data processing records;
and
Protecting the Company's rights and defense against legal claims.
Note to our Users in the EU and UK:
In order for Boards to process your Personal Information, as detailed herein, such processing must be justified by a "lawful basis" for processing. Please note that the Personal Information processing activities detailed herein may be justified on the basis that:
the processing is based on your consent
- where you provide us with your consent to process your Personal Information for one or more specific purposes. For instance, before we contact you for electronic marketing purposes, you will be asked to consent to our processing of your Personal Information for this purpose. If you choose not to provide your consent for such processing activities, or if you decide later on to revoke your consent, this will affect our ability to provide you with Boards's marketing materials;
the processing is necessary for performance of a contract to which you are party
- generally your Personal Information will be provided to us because you are interested in using the Site and/or App and/or Services in accordance with the TOU or in order to receive certain services from Boards. As such, we rely on this basis for processing activities that are required in order to enable you to use the App and/or Site and to provide our Services and to let you know of changes to our TOU and Privacy Policy;
the processing is necessary to comply with a legal obligation
- we may process your Personal Information for disclosure of information to authorities and to comply with our legal obligations (e.g., paying taxes); and
the processing is necessary for the purposes of our legitimate commercial interests
- subject to your interests and fundamental rights, processing of Personal Information will take place pursuant to our legitimate interests in offering our Users comfortable, effective and safe access to our Site and App. This shall include the processing of your Personal Information in order to personalize the Site and/or App, assist us in preventing crime and fraud and manage our internal operations. Where we rely on legitimate interests as a lawful basis, we carry out a balancing test to ensure that your interests, rights and freedoms do not override our legitimate interests.
Note to non-EU and non-UK Users:
BY ENTERING, CONNECTING TO, ACCESSING OR USING THE SITE AND/OR APP, YOU CONSENT TO THE COLLECTION AND PROCESSING OF YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION AS SPECIFIED HEREIN.
